Business Meaning
Positive residuals indicate stores that exceeded expectations.
Negative residuals indicate stores that underperformed relative to expectations.
Residual analysis helps identify unusual store performance and potential missing business factors.
Some stores may be influenced by local events, promotions, competition, or operational differences not included in the model.
Model Evaluation

The model performs reasonably well with an R² value of approximately 0.782. However, several stores show large residual values, indicating that additional variables could improve prediction accuracy.

Conclusion

The regression model explains a large portion of sales variation but does not capture all factors affecting store performance. Residual analysis highlights stores where actual performance differs substantially from predictions, suggesting opportunities for further investigation and model improvement.
